The `name` property is the unique identifier.
An InconsistentAttributes node will only exist if there are differences (inconsistencies)
within the attributes of one specific term. There will be always at least one
other InconsistentAttributes node with different attributes for the same term.
If no InconsistentAttributes node exist, the Term node contains consistent attributes.
The same concept holds true for codelists.
